# This directory is the shared control channel between the CMMS web container
# and the host-side updater agent (scripts/host-updater.sh).
#
# At runtime it holds:
#   requests/<uuid>.json  - update requests written by the webapp (SUPER_ADMIN button)
#   status.json           - current/remote commit + last result, written by the host agent
#   logs/<uuid>.log       - per-update output captured by the host agent
#   *.lock                - flock guard
#
# All of the above is runtime state and is gitignored (see .gitignore). This
# .gitkeep keeps the empty directory in the repo so the docker-compose bind mount
# (./deploy-control:/app/deploy-control) has something to mount on a fresh clone.
